Algorithm Formulas

Epanechnikov Kernel
\( K(u) = \frac{3}{4}(1 - u^2) \cdot \mathbf{1}_{|u| \leq 1} \)
Scaled Distance
\( u_i = \frac{x_i - x_0}{h} \)
Weighted Median
\( \hat{y}(x_0) = \text{wmedian}\{y_i : w_i = K(u_i)\} \)

Key Insight

The weighted median ignores the magnitude of outliers - only their position in the sorted order matters. This makes it robust to extreme values that would heavily influence the weighted mean.
